column5: A beautiful Mills fish... and a good picture that shows it's length. There is another shot available that shows just how fat she was as well.  Foot and a half of new snow in the last 36 hours here in the buckle of the snow belt. Don't think I can find a usable launch...
Found  this on another site.It was posted last night ,was reportedly 55x28.5 and caught on georgian bay.
Son of a gun!
oh no....
Mills knows how to put the big ones in the boat for sure.
Good lord. Another monster!  Yep, putting the boat away early
Wow that's a nice one,
dang I wish I could figure them out on GB...greatc fish
As Borat would say... Veryyyy Niiiiice....."
Jealous Pete
You and Glen should go giver soon
that old muskie is a war pig... huge though!
I think that fish was caught 3 weeks ago.  How about posting the thread you got it from?
Awesome fish for sure !!!!
Wow! Nice fish...... Amazes me how these pigs can still have the speed to feed.  Maybe that's why they seem to be chasing lures going by at only 3-5 mph these last few days.  Great Job angler

All fish slow down when the water gets cold... including the bait! The Musky have just as good of a chance to get a meal now as they did in the summer.  The Musky weight calculator puts a 55x28.5 at just a Gnats ass under 56 lbs.
Yep , That falls into the '' Serious Beast catergory ''
The fish has a bigger head than the angler.  If only fish could talk..
yeah, monster. Jodi knows how to do it!  what a fish!
THATS HUGE, congradulations to the guy who caught that giant. I can only imagine...
Oh my...  Hmm, my boats in the garage but these threads are beginning to make her want to see water next weekend...Congratulations again are in order to the lucky angler.
Icouldn't agree more,I mean 10 to 15cm of snow and low of minus 11 doesn't sound all that bad.See you out there
Were doing a musky trip to the Upper Niagara on the 13th Jigger, why not drag the boat outta the garage & join us

Thanks for the invite Lew! I was thinking water a little more on the smaller side seeing as I only have a 14 footer. I've seen the pics of the past few trips you guys made at his time of year. Looks like it can get pretty hairy out there! Maybe someone has a spot open? I'm guessing theres a sticky up so I'll check in there.Now I just have to slide it past the warden   .
Speechless
This is nice, all the kids are playing together nicely.  Nice feesh too.
